Example demonstrating Array grimoire functionality in Carrion.

This script shows how to create arrays and use the Array grimoire
for enhanced array operations like appending elements. The Array
grimoire provides object-oriented methods for array manipulation
beyond the basic array literal syntax.
```

# Create an initial array with integer values
x = [10, 9, 8, 4, 1]

# Wrap the array in an Array grimoire for enhanced functionality
arr = Array(x)

# Use the Array grimoire's append method to add a new element
arr.append(11)

